<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Bicycle_and_motorcycle_dynamics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=49" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.dclxvi.org/chunk/tech/trail/" class="external text" title="http://www.dclxvi.org/chunk/tech/trail/" rel="nofollow">‘An Introduction to Bicycle Geometry and Handling’</a>, Karl Anderson</li>
<li><a href="http://diablocyclists.org/DCtechtips.html" class="external text" title="http://diablocyclists.org/DCtechtips.html" rel="nofollow">‘Interesting Bike Science’</a> by Paul Pedriana</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sheldonbrown.com/brandt/gyro.html" class="external text" title="http://www.sheldonbrown.com/brandt/gyro.html" rel="nofollow">‘What keeps the bicycle upright?’</a> by Jobst Brandt</li>
<li><a href="http://www.johnforester.com/Articles/BicycleEng/dahon.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.johnforester.com/Articles/BicycleEng/dahon.htm" rel="nofollow">‘Report on Stability of the Dahon Bicycle’</a> by John Forester</li>
</ul>
